qas.question: What private schools are in the Eastern School District?

context: St. John's is served by the <b5_0>Eastern School District<b5_0/>, the largest school district in Newfoundland and Labrador by student population. There are currently <a1_0><b6_0>36<b6_0/><a1_0/> primary, elementary and secondary schools in the city of St. John's, including <a0_0>three<a0_0/> private schools. St. John's also includes one school that is part of the province-wide Conseil Scolaire Francophone (CSF), the Francophone public school district. It also contains <a2_0>two<a2_0/> private schools, <b7_0>St. Bonaventure's College and Lakecrest Independent<b7_0/>. Atlantic Canada's largest university, Memorial University of Newfoundland (MUN), is located in St. John's. MUN provides comprehensive education and grants degrees in several fields and its historical strengths in engineering, business, geology, and medicine, make MUN one of the top comprehensive universities in Canada. The Fisheries and Marine Institute of <a3_0>Memorial University of Newfoundland<a3_0/> (MI) or simply Marine Institute, is a post-secondary ocean and marine polytechnic located in St. John's and is affiliated with Memorial University of Newfoundland. MUN also offers the lowest tuition in Canada (<a4_0>$2,644<a4_0/>, per Academic Year)
